Class TyDemoActivationCSFactory

  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    TymeacInterface, java.io.Serializable, java.rmi.Remote

    public class TyDemoActivationCSFactory
extends TymeacActivationImpl
    Tymeac Demonstration System. This Class is an example of how to inherit the Tymeac Activation Implementation of the TymeacInterface interface for a custom socket factory. When developing an activation description activation.ActivationDesc() the name of the Class to be activated is needed. This Class is TymeacActivationCSFactoryImpl. However, you may wish to have several of these remote objects in any one system. If there is only one name, then there can only be one occurance. Therefore, by extending the main Class, TymeacActivationCSFactoryImpl, and overriding its constructor, you may have as many names as you wish for activatable remote objects. This Class is an example of how you may do this.
